@startuml 25_D1_Detection_Flow
!theme plain

skinparam backgroundColor #F5F7FA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam Padding 5
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.5

skinparam title {
  FontSize 17
  FontStyle bold
  FontColor #1A237E
  BackgroundColor #E8EAF6
  BorderColor #3F51B5
  BorderThickness 2
}

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #455A64
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
  BorderColor #FFB300
  FontColor #4E342E
  FontSize 10
  BorderThickness 1.5
}

title <b>3D Data Quality Framework · D1 Detection Layer</b>\n<size:12>Multi-Source Triggers -> Pipeline | DAD | ITSM | Platform | SLA Agents -> Anomaly Handover to D2</size>

participant "Workflows\nonFailure\n[Pipeline]"        as T_PIPE  #D1C4E9
participant "Delta CDF\n[DAD Trigger]"                as T_DAD   #D1C4E9
participant "Scheduled\n+ HISTORY\n[SLA]"             as T_SLA   #D1C4E9
participant "Jira Webhook\n[ITSM]"                    as T_ITSM  #D1C4E9
participant "Pipeline\nAgent"                         as PA      #FFCDD2
participant "DAD Agent\n[Data Anomaly\nDetection]"    as DAD     #FFCDD2
participant "SLA\nAgent"                              as SLAA    #FFCDD2
participant "ITSM\nAgent"                             as ITSMA   #FFCDD2
participant "Platform\nAgent"                         as PLAT    #FFCDD2
database    "anomaly_check_config\n(Delta)"           as RuleDB
database    "table_daily_metrics\n(Delta baselines)"  as Metrics
database    "DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n(Delta sink)"    as AnomalyDB
database    "check_execution_log\n(Delta)"            as ExecLog
database    "rule_audit_log\n(Delta)"                 as AuditLog
participant "DESCRIBE DETAIL\n+ HISTORY (UC)"         as UCMeta
participant "D2 Diagnosis\nEngine"                    as D2

== [D1-0]  Rule and Baseline Bootstrap ==

note over PA, PLAT
  All five agents share a common bootstrap phase at job start.
  Rules and baselines are loaded ONCE per Databricks job cycle.
end note

PA -> RuleDB : SELECT * FROM anomaly_check_config\nWHERE is_active = true\nORDER BY priority ASC
RuleDB --> PA : active_rules[]

PA -> Metrics : SELECT table_name, mean_rows, stddev_rows,\n  freshness_sla_hours, rolling_30d_pass_rate\nFROM table_daily_metrics
Metrics --> PA : baselines_map

PA -> UCMeta : DESCRIBE DETAIL + DESCRIBE HISTORY LIMIT 50\n(once per table_fqn in active_rules)
UCMeta --> PA : {last_modified, row_count, schema_version}

note right of PA
  Metadata cached in-memory for the job run.
  Prevents repeated UC API calls per check.
end note

== [D1-1]  Pipeline Agent -- Workflows onFailure ==

T_PIPE -> PA : onFailure webhook\n{job_id, run_id, task_key, error_message, failed_at}
activate PA

note right of PA
  Handles structural failures:\n  - ADF pipeline Bronze/Silver gap\n  - Databricks Workflow task error\n  - Job skipped or timed out\n  - Upstream dependency not met
end note

PA -> ExecLog : INSERT check_execution_log\n{agent='PIPELINE', trigger='WORKFLOW_FAILURE', job_id, detected_at}
PA -> AnomalyDB : INSERT DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n{anomaly_type='PIPELINE_FAILURE', source_job_id,\n affected_tables[], severity=P1, status='DETECTED'}
AnomalyDB --> PA : anomaly_id = DA_20260701_001
PA -> AuditLog : LOG {agent='PIPELINE', event='ANOMALY_RAISED', anomaly_id, severity=P1}
deactivate PA

== [D1-2]  DAD Agent -- Data Anomaly Detection via Delta CDF ==

T_DAD -> DAD : Delta CDF event\n{table_name, commit_version,\n change_type: INSERT|UPDATE|DELETE, changed_rows_count}
activate DAD

note right of DAD
  DAD = Data Anomaly Detection engine.\n  Consumes Delta CDF to detect:\n  - Volume DROP  (rows < baseline x 0.80)\n  - Unexpected bulk DELETE\n  - Distribution SHIFT  (Z-score > 3 sigma)\n  - NULL SPIKE  (null_rate > threshold)\n  - OUTLIER SURGE (statistical cluster breach)\n  All checks driven by anomaly_check_config rules.
end note

DAD -> RuleDB : SELECT check_sql, check_type, threshold, z_score_band\nFROM anomaly_check_config\nWHERE table_name = :table AND is_active = true
RuleDB --> DAD : matching_rules[]

loop For each active rule on this table
  DAD -> ExecLog : Execute check_sql via Spark (SELECT-only)
  ExecLog --> DAD : {actual_value, violation_pct, z_score}

  alt Check FAILS
    DAD -> Metrics : Compare vs 30-day baseline
    Metrics --> DAD : {expected_range, deviation_factor}
    DAD -> AnomalyDB : INSERT DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n{anomaly_type=check_type, table_name, column_name,\n violation_pct, z_score, severity=P1|P2|P3, status='DETECTED'}
    AnomalyDB --> DAD : anomaly_id
    DAD -> ExecLog : UPDATE check_execution_log SET result='FAIL', anomaly_id=:id
  else Check PASSES
    DAD -> ExecLog : UPDATE check_execution_log SET result='PASS'
  end
end

DAD -> Metrics : UPDATE table_daily_metrics\nSET last_run_at=NOW(), rolling_pass_rate=recalculated
deactivate DAD

== [D1-3]  SLA Agent -- Scheduled Freshness Check via HISTORY ==

T_SLA -> SLAA : Scheduled cron trigger\n+ DESCRIBE HISTORY on monitored tables
activate SLAA

note right of SLAA
  Enforces freshness contracts:\n  - Reads last commit from DESCRIBE HISTORY\n  - Compares to freshness_sla_hours in config\n  - Flags FRESHNESS_DRIFT if overdue\n  - Also checks row_count vs 7-day rolling mean
end note

SLAA -> UCMeta : DESCRIBE HISTORY <table> LIMIT 1 -> last_commit_timestamp
UCMeta --> SLAA : {version, timestamp, operation}

SLAA -> RuleDB : SELECT freshness_sla_hours FROM anomaly_check_config\nWHERE check_type='FRESHNESS' AND table_name=:table
RuleDB --> SLAA : sla_config

alt SLA VIOLATED  (hours_since_update > freshness_sla_hours)
  SLAA -> AnomalyDB : INSERT DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n{anomaly_type='FRESHNESS_DRIFT',\n hours_since_update, sla_threshold_hours,\n severity=P1 (>2x SLA) | P2 (>1x SLA), status='DETECTED'}
  AnomalyDB --> SLAA : anomaly_id
  SLAA -> ExecLog : INSERT {agent='SLA', result='FAIL', anomaly_id}
  SLAA -> AuditLog : LOG {event='SLA_BREACH', table, sla_hours, actual_hours}
else SLA MET
  SLAA -> ExecLog : INSERT {agent='SLA', result='PASS'}
end
deactivate SLAA

== [D1-4]  ITSM Agent -- Jira Webhook ==

T_ITSM -> ITSMA : Jira webhook\n{issue_key, summary, priority, affected_table, reporter}
activate ITSMA

note right of ITSMA
  Bridges manual reports into D1 pipeline:\n  - Parses Jira fields -> table + domain context\n  - Creates anomaly record for D2 automated diagnosis\n  - Links anomaly_id back to Jira (bi-directional)\n  - Priority mapping: Jira P1->DRE P1, P2->P2, P3/4->P3
end note

ITSMA -> AnomalyDB : INSERT DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n{anomaly_type='ITSM_REPORTED', source_ticket=issue_key,\n affected_table, severity mapped from Jira priority,\n status='DETECTED', diagnosis_hint='manual_report'}
AnomalyDB --> ITSMA : anomaly_id
ITSMA -> ExecLog : INSERT {agent='ITSM', trigger='JIRA_WEBHOOK', issue_key, anomaly_id}
ITSMA -> AuditLog : LOG {event='ITSM_INGESTED', issue_key, anomaly_id}
deactivate ITSMA

== [D1-5]  Platform Agent -- Infrastructure Monitoring ==

T_SLA -> PLAT : Scheduled platform-health scan
activate PLAT

note right of PLAT
  Monitors platform-level signals:\n  - Cluster health and job queue depth\n  - Token budget utilisation\n  - Cache hit rate for suggestion cache\n  Runs alongside the SLA Agent cron.
end note

PLAT -> UCMeta : SHOW JOBS + cluster metrics API\n{active_jobs, failed_jobs_last_1h, token_budget_pct}
UCMeta --> PLAT : platform_metrics

alt Platform anomaly  (>10% job failures in 1h OR token budget < 15%)
  PLAT -> AnomalyDB : INSERT DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n{anomaly_type='PLATFORM_DEGRADATION',\n component, metric, observed_value,\n severity=P2|P3, status='DETECTED'}
  AnomalyDB --> PLAT : anomaly_id
  PLAT -> ExecLog : INSERT {agent='PLATFORM', result='FAIL', anomaly_id}
else Platform healthy
  PLAT -> ExecLog : INSERT {agent='PLATFORM', result='PASS'}
end
deactivate PLAT

== [D1-6]  Severity Triage and DRRI Score Update ==

note over PA, PLAT
  After all agents complete their detection pass:\n  - DRRI recalculated: (rules_passed / rules_executed) x freshness_weight x coverage_weight\n  - Score written back to table_daily_metrics\n  - P1 anomalies -> immediate D2 handover\n  - P2/P3 -> batched for next D2 cycle
end note

DAD -> Metrics : UPDATE table_daily_metrics\nSET drri_score = (rules_passed / rules_executed x freshness_weight x coverage_weight)\nWHERE domain=:domain AND run_date=TODAY()
Metrics --> DAD : drri_scores_updated

== [D1-7]  Anomaly Handover to D2 Diagnosis Engine ==

AnomalyDB -> D2 : SELECT * FROM DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\nWHERE status='DETECTED' AND diagnosis_status='PENDING'\nORDER BY severity ASC, detected_at ASC

note right of D2
  D2 receives anomaly token:\n  {anomaly_id, anomaly_type, table_name,\n   violation_pct, z_score, severity, detected_at}\n  D2 starts: Drift Classifier -> Lineage Tracer\n  -> Segment Slicer -> Evidence Retriever\n  -> Playbook Compiler.\n  See: 15_d2_diagnosis_flow.puml
end note

AnomalyDB -> AnomalyDB : UPDATE SET diagnosis_status='IN_PROGRESS'\nWHERE anomaly_id IN (:handed_over_ids)

@enduml